# Tailwind Theme-Only Classes Rule

Kitchen-Craft uses a strict design system powered by Tailwind CSS `theme()` tokens. **Do not** use hard-coded colour utilities like `text-gray-500`, `bg-red-600`, `border-slate-200`, etc.

## Allowed
• `text-primary`, `bg-secondary`, `border-input`, etc. (Tokens defined in `tailwind.config.ts`).
• Programmatic usage: `className={cn('text-muted', condition && 'bg-accent')}` where all classes come from theme.

## Disallowed
• Any colour class that encodes numeric shade or direct colour, e.g. `text-gray-500`, `bg-[#ff0000]`.
• Arbitrary hex/RGB values in `className` or inline style.

## Migration
When encountering disallowed classes:
1. Map to closest token in design system.
2. If missing, extend palette in `tailwind.config.ts`.

CI should fail if lint detects banned patterns. Reviewers must enforce this rule.

> Tip: Use Tailwind IntelliSense to autocomplete theme tokens.